[[Image:Seychelles Governor inspection 1972.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Sir Bruce Greatbatch inspecting police guard of honour on the Seychelles in 1972]]
'''Sir Bruce Greatbatch''', [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]], [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]], [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (10 June 1917 – 20 July 1989) <ref>http://www.leighrayment.com/knights/knightsfoxgz.htm</ref> was the [[Great Britain|British]] colonial governor of [[Seychelles]] from 1969 to 1973. He was educated at [[Malvern College]] and [[Brasenose College, Oxford]].<ref>2007 "Greatbatch, Sir Bruce, (10 June 1917–20 July 1989)." WHO'S WHO & WHO WAS WHO</ref> He oversaw the [[Depopulation of Chagossians from the Chagos Archipelago|forced removal of the indigenous people]] of the [[Chagos Archipelago]] and ordered the gassing of the islander's pet dog population of 1,000. He called the Chagossians "unsophisticated" and "untrainable". The evacuation was carried out in order to construct an [[United States|American]] military installation on [[Diego Garcia]].

