{{expand Ukrainian|Коноплі в Україні|date=January 2017}}
{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}
'''[[Cannabis]] in [[Ukraine]]''' is illegal, but continues to be produced illicitly.

==History==
[[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Soviet Ukraine]] was one of the biggest producers of hemp, and before the 1950s, it had over 150.000 hectares dedicated to hemp cultivation.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}} Cannabis wasn't widely used as a recreational drug in [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Soviet Ukraine]], most of the grown [[hemp]] would be used for it's other natural resources such as oil and fiber.<ref>http://www.internationalhempassociation.org/jiha/iha02113.html</ref>

During the [[Soviet–Afghan War|Soviet-Afghan war]], [[Charas]] (Чарас) were often bought from [[Afghan]] children and then smoked by [[Soviet Army|Soviet soldiers]], it would usually get smuggled into the [[Soviet Union]] by returning soldiers.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}

==Production==
Cannabis that is suitable for recreational use is often grown in small plantations, hidden amongst corn, in black soil suitable for cultivation which is found in the central and southern parts of the country.

Though illegal, a lot of [[Cannabis ruderalis|Cannabis Ruderalis]] is grown out in the open in small villages for mostly non-recreational use, because of the low amount of [[Tetrahydrocannabinol|THC]] in [[Cannabis ruderalis|C. Ruderalis]].

==Enforcement==
According to Article 106-2 [[KUoAP]], cultivation (without intent to sell) up to 10 cannabis plants qualifies as an administrative violation, with a fine of from 18 to 100 non-taxable income units (300-1700 [[hryvnia]] in 2011) and the seizure of plants.<ref name="rada.gov.ua20090319">{{Cite web| last = Ющенко| first = Віктор| title = Про внесення змін до Кодексу України про адміністративні правопорушення та Кримінального кодексу України щодо посилення відповідальності за незаконний посів або незаконне вирощування снотворного маку чи конопель (№ 1165-VI)| work = Верховна Рада України| date = 2009-03-19| url = http://zakon4.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/1165-17/print1462851647388498}}</ref>

The limit for possession without intent to sell, for which no criminal liability is given, is up to 5 grams of cannabis.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}} However, there are plans to raise this limit to 10 grams.<ref>[http://www.golosua.com/ua/main/article/podiyi/20100701_dopustimu-mezhu-zberigannya-marihuani-planuyut-zbi ]{{dead link|date=January 2017}}</ref>

==Reform==
===2016 protests===
In October 2016, pro-cannabis protestors and anti-cannabis counter-protestors faced off in [[Mikhaylivska Square]] in Kiev. Police were forced to restrain some protestors from fighting each other.<ref>{{cite web|last=Davies |first=Gareth |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3885902/Your-cannabis-protest-gone-pot-Ukrainian-riot-police-called-pin-nationalists-trying-prevent-rally-support-legalising-marijuana.html |title=Ukrainian riot police called to prevent a rally in support of legalising marijuana &#124; Daily Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-01-26}}</ref>

=== 2017 Cannabis March of Freedom ===
A march was planned for October 28, 2017, taking place near the Government of Ukraine.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/events/602642196606568/permalink/662572530613534/ 2017 Cannabis March of Freedom in Ukraine]. Facebook</ref><ref>https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/freedom-march-decriminalize-marijuana-personal-use-planned-kyiv.html</ref>

