{{Politics of Gabon}}

The '''Democratic and Republican Alliance''' ({{Lang-fr|Alliance Démocratique et Républicaine}}, ADERE) is a [[political party]] in [[Gabon]].

==History==
The party won a single seat in the [[Gabonese legislative election, 1996|1996 parliamentary elections]]. It gained two more seats in the [[Gabonese legislative election, 2001|2001 elections]] and retained all three seats in the [[Gabonese legislative election, 2006|2006 elections]], in which it was part of the bloc led by the ruling [[Gabonese Democratic Party]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/ga.html Elections in Gabon] African Elections Database</ref>

At a plenary session on 15 January 2010, ADERE decided to rejoin the Presidential Majority, which it had left in mid-2009, while expressing support for the reforms instituted by President [[Ali Bongo Ondimba|Ali Bongo]] since taking office.<ref>[http://gaboneco.com/show_article.php?IDActu=16584 "Gabon : Divungi fait son come-back dans la cour de Bongo"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100122210044/http://www.gaboneco.com/show_article.php?IDActu=16584 |date=22 January 2010 }}, Gaboneco, 16 January 2010 {{fr icon}}.</ref> The party lost all three seats in the [[Gabonese legislative election, 2011|2011 elections]].

ADERE President [[Dieudonné Pambou]] died on 24 January 2014.<ref>[http://www.gaboneco.com/nouvelles_africaines_31612.html "L’Adere en deuil : Décès de Dieudonné Pambou"], Gaboneco, 27 January 2014 {{fr icon}}</ref>

