{{Infobox Union |name= iooo |country= [[Uzbekistan]] |affiliation= [[General Confederation of Trade Unions|GCTU]] |members= |full_name= Federation of Trade Unions of Uzbekistan |native_name= |image= |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Tashkent]], Uzbekistan |people= [[Dilbar Djikhangirova]], president |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Federation of Trade Unions of Uzbekistan''' (FTUU), also known as the '''Trade Unions Federation of Uzbekistan''' (TUFU) is the sole [[national trade union center]] in [[Uzbekistan]]. It is the remnant of the previous [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] trade union system, although it has lost some of its previous powers, such as state planning and enterprise management.
The FTUU is affiliated to the [[General Confederation of Trade Unions]].
