'''Hrvatska Lutrija''' ({{lang-en|Croatian Lottery}}) is the national [[lottery]] of [[Croatia]].
== History ==
In 1951 was established as the ''Directorate for Croatia'' ({{lang-hr|Direkcija za Hrvatsku}}), which was a part of the Yugoslav Lottery.
In 1973 it became independent organization for the Croatian lottery, although remained part of the Business community of Yugoslav lotteries.
In 1993, two years after Croatia became an independent country, the lottery was renamed to Hrvatska Lutrija d.o.o.<ref>https://www.lutrija.hr/cms/Kratkapovijest</ref>
