The '''Kel Ferwan''' are a [[Tuareg people|Tuareg]] nomadic clan, who have historically been a subgroup of the [[Kel Ayr]] confederation. In the 20th century, they have mostly been based in the [[Aïr Mountains]] of north central [[Niger]].

